title: Empty plots-poses after analysing video
body:
### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the existing issues

### Bug description

 I’ve trained and evaluated my model and it all works fine up to this stage, but when I try to plot the trajectories under the tab Analyse videos, the outputs are four empty graphs. I’ve attached one of the graphs here
![plot-likelihood_filtered](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/27425366/172090842-912b05fb-5201-435a-82f1-dcb753c3ee55.png)
:
Also, in my case the issue is not the p-value cut off. Setting it as low as possible does not repopulate the plots. And the p-values for the frames are pretty much all >.9 for my csv files.

### Operating System

os:windows 10

### DeepLabCut version

dlc version:2.2.1

### DeepLabCut mode

single animal

### Device type

gpu:3080

### Steps To Reproduce

I folllowed the instroduction step by step:
Interactive Project Manager GUI[https://deeplabcut.github.io/DeepLabCut/docs/PROJECT_GUI.html](url)
